<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  officraft — EXECUTION-plane warden (golang) launchd job TEMPLATE.

  Label `com.officraft.ocwarden` is the CANONICAL warden label. It is distinct
  from the retired python daemons' labels (`com.officraft.warden` pull warden,
  `com.officraft.telemetry` telemetry warden), so the flip installs ONE final
  label with no coexistence-window collision: launchd cannot load two jobs under
  one label, and choosing a fresh canonical name (rather than recycling the old
  `com.officraft.warden`) means the golang job can be bootstrapped WHILE the
  python jobs still run, then — and only then — the python jobs are booted out.
  The brief pull+push overlap is idempotent (tmux clobber-guard on spawn,
  isMemberSession gate on kill). See cli/ocwarden/CUTOVER.md.

  Own log files (ocwarden.*) — NOT the python jobs' warden.* — so nothing
  interleaves writes during the coexistence window.

  BUILD-TO-READY, NOT INSTALLED. This file lives in-repo as a reviewable template;
  it is NOT copied into ~/Library/LaunchAgents until the gated flip.

  REFERENCE TEMPLATE — NOT installed verbatim. The __ROOT__ / __OC_BASE__ / __HOME__
  tokens below are placeholders. The AUTHORITATIVE renderer is `ocwarden install`
  (renderPlist in cli/ocwarden/install.go; the flip-era bash bin/warden-install is
  retired), which substitutes the real per-machine repo ROOT, OC_BASE and HOME at install time
  and writes the result to ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.officraft.ocwarden.plist.
  This file is therefore never `cp`'d as-is (it would fail to launch: __ROOT__ is not
  a path) — it exists to document the shape a reviewer signs off on. There is ONE
  path truth: the installer; this template deliberately holds no real path.

  Execs the self-contained binary bin/ocwarden DIRECTLY (the former bin/warden-go
  wrapper is folded in): the binary reads OC_WARDEN_TOKFILE to resolve the
  execution-plane warden token/id itself, then the command reader starts
  unconditionally. Distinct from com.officraft.telemetry (hardware telemetry).
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key><string>com.officraft.ocwarden</string>
    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array><string>__ROOT__/bin/ocwarden</string><string>run</string></array>
    <key>WorkingDirectory</key><string>__ROOT__</string>
    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>PATH</key><string>/opt/homebrew/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin</string>
        <key>OC_BASE</key><string>__OC_BASE__</string>
        <key>HOME</key><string>__HOME__</string>
        <key>OC_WARDEN_TOKFILE</key><string>__HOME__/.officraft/warden/exec-warden.tok</string>
        <!-- CONDITIONAL (renderPlist): OC_NAMESPACE for a namespaced instance, and
             OC_CLAUDE_BIN when the install resolved a claude executable — the
             minimal launchd PATH above cannot re-find a version-manager claude at
             runtime, so the installer stamps the absolute path here (and swaps
             PATH for the installer's PATH when claude is a shim that needs it).
        <key>OC_CLAUDE_BIN</key><string>__CLAUDE_BIN__</string>
        -->
    </dict>
    <key>RunAtLoad</key><true/>
    <key>KeepAlive</key><true/>
    <key>ThrottleInterval</key><integer>10</integer>
    <key>StandardOutPath</key><string>__ROOT__/var/log/ocwarden.out.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key><string>__ROOT__/var/log/ocwarden.err.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
